      "id": "bug-delivery-start-trip",
      "timestamp": "2026-05-27T00:00:00.000Z",
      "error_message": "Delivery dashboard 'ابدأ التوصيل' button does nothing on click",
      "file": "app/delivery/delivery-panel.tsx",
      "root_cause": "OrderCard.handleAdvance ignored updateDeliveryOrderStatus's return value (silently dropped {error}), and DeliveryPanel seeded `orders` via useState(initialOrders) without resyncing when revalidatePath delivered new server props. The action's 'use server' update used .eq() with no .select(), so an RLS-blocked 0-row update returned no error and no rows -- producing silent failure paths.",
      "fix": "1) lib/actions/delivery.ts: chain .select('id').maybeSingle() on the update and surface a 0-row case as { error }; have listDeliveryOrders throw on error so the caller can show an offline banner. 2) app/delivery/delivery-panel.tsx: rewrote OrderCard with a parent-supplied onTransition that does optimistic local update, calls the action, rolls back + shows a per-card red error banner on failure, then refetches authoritative state. Added useEffect to resync local orders when initialOrders prop changes, a 'آخر تحديث' clock, manual refresh button, pulsing live indicators on pending/on_delivery chips, spinner+'جاري التحديث…' on in-flight buttons, and a SUBSCRIBED-triggered refetch so realtime catch-up works. 3) app/delivery/page.tsx: try/catch around the now-throwing listDeliveryOrders.",
      "tags": [
        "delivery",
        "rls",
        "optimistic-ui",
        "realtime",
